# Phalanges of Foot

> The foot contains **14 phalanges**. The great toe (Hallux) has 2; each of the other four toes has 3.

## 🔗 Connected Structures
- [[Metatarsals]] — **Metatarsophalangeal joints (MTP joints)**
- Interphalangeal joints:
  - **PIP joint** — Proximal ↔ middle phalanx
  - **DIP joint** — Middle ↔ distal phalanx

## 🗂️ Components

| Segment          | Count | Description                           |
| ---------------- | ----- | ------------------------------------- |
| Proximal phalanx | 5     | MTP & PIP joint formation             |
| Middle phalanx   | 4     | Absent in great toe; PIP & DIP joints |
| Distal phalanx   | 5     | Supports toenail                      |

## 🔑 Great Toe (Hallux)
- 2 sesamoid bones beneath the 1st MTP joint
- Critical role in push-off phase of gait
- **Hallux valgus** — lateral deviation at the 1st MTP joint

## 🏥 Clinical Significance
- **Hallux valgus** — 1st MTP lateral deviation; bunion; common in adult women
- **Hammer toe** — PIP flexion deformity; dorsal corn formation
- **Claw toe** — MTP hyperextension + PIP/DIP flexion
- **Toe fractures** — Direct trauma (stubbing or dropped object)
- **Gout (Podagra)** — 1st MTP joint; monosodium urate crystal deposition


